# E2E pytest marker (SOP)

GitHub Actions **server / e2e (preview)** runs:

`uv run pytest -v -m e2e`

Only tests marked with **`@pytest.mark.e2e`** are collected. Tests without this marker **do not run in CI** and **will not appear** in the Action log.

## Required for every E2E test

- Add **`@pytest.mark.e2e`** on each test function (or use module-level `pytestmark = pytest.mark.e2e` if the whole file is E2E-only).
- Async E2E tests can combine markers, e.g. `@pytest.mark.e2e` then `@pytest.mark.anyio` (or rely on `pytest-asyncio` like sibling tests — match existing files in `server/tests/e2e/`).
- Optional subset: **`@pytest.mark.smoke`** for tests included in `pytest -m smoke` (staging); keep **`e2e`** regardless unless the test is intentionally not part of preview E2E.

## Reference

- Marker definition: `server/pyproject.toml` → `[tool.pytest.ini_options].markers`
- Workflow: `.github/workflows/server-ci.yml` → step "Run E2E pytest subset"
